00:33:16.000 --> 00:33:18.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
Some nights,

00:33:18.000 --> 00:33:24.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
I wake up choking to the woman inside of me trying to claw her way out of my mouth.

00:33:24.000 --> 00:33:30.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
She waits until I am sleeping because it is the only time I do not try to forget her.

00:33:30.000 --> 00:33:37.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
Sometimes, when I am alone, I can hear her weeping in between the times I inhale and exhale.

00:33:37.000 --> 00:33:42.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
When I bind my chest, I feel more than just the suffocation of my body,

00:33:42.000 --> 00:33:46.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
I feel hurt inside of me, gasping for air.

00:33:46.000 --> 00:33:50.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
I know she is terrified I am trying to squeeze her out of me for good.

00:33:50.000 --> 00:33:56.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
For a while, I tried. I swallowed her in front of other men to not seem weak.

00:33:56.000 --> 00:34:00.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
I stiffened up every time I felt her welling up behind my eyes.

00:34:00.000 --> 00:34:04.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
Used her as a scapegoat the times anger was the only prayer in my mouth.

00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:08.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
Blamed her for the depression, the anxiety, the dysphoria,

00:34:08.000 --> 00:34:12.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
the dirty looks in public restrooms and fitting rooms for being a goddamn box

00:34:12.000 --> 00:34:16.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
To check on paperwork, I hated her for having the audacity to stay

00:34:16.000 --> 00:34:19.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
even after I demanded her to leave.

00:34:19.000 --> 00:34:23.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
I also mourned, and I grieved.

00:34:23.000 --> 00:34:28.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
I didn't know how to say goodbye, I didn't know if I had to.

00:34:28.000 --> 00:34:34.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
When my therapist told me I have internalized misogyny, I cried.

00:34:34.000 --> 00:34:38.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
Until the woman in me finally poured out my eyes and onto the floor

00:34:38.000 --> 00:34:43.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
She has never said I told you so, she has only ever offered me a book of poems

00:34:43.000 --> 00:34:47.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
written by the person I used to be, and now, here, in front of this mirror that I

00:34:47.000 --> 00:34:49.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
that I begged to tell me lies,

00:34:49.000 --> 00:34:52.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
I am desperately looking for something that resembles something familiar

00:34:52.000 --> 00:34:57.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
but I've only ever performed by poems in a higher pitch and I fear a lower frequency

00:34:57.000 --> 00:35:02.000 line:13 position:0% align:left size:100% background:black color:white
